This product includes software developed by the janus-camera-stack
contributors.

Third-party components shipped with or required by this software:

- Janus Gateway SERVER (https://janus.conf.meetecho.com/) — GPL v3
  Not vendored; a runtime dependency, built from source by deploy/janus/Dockerfile
  or run natively. The server is a separate process — this software interoperates
  with it over its network API (aggregation), it is not linked into it.

- janus.js BROWSER CLIENT (Meetecho) — MIT
  Vendored at templates/janus.js (MIT is compatible with this project's Apache-2.0
  license). The MIT copyright header is retained in the file. Refresh/upgrade with
  scripts/fetch-janus-js.sh.

- coturn (https://github.com/coturn/coturn) — BSD-3-Clause
  Not vendored; configured as runtime dependency.

- FastAPI (https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/) — MIT
- uvicorn (https://www.uvicorn.org/) — BSD-3-Clause
- httpx, pydantic, jinja2, prometheus-client, websockets, starlette
  Listed in requirements.txt; each retains its original license.

- pyrealsense2 (Intel RealSense SDK) — Apache-2.0
  Optional, used by realsense_mux.py on edge nodes with D435/D435i hardware.

When redistributing janus-camera-stack bundled with these dependencies,
preserve their respective LICENSE / NOTICE files.
